{"id": "seminar-ideaeng-2f8a1c07-4b6e-4d21-9a3c-wwu2026", "name": "IdeaM Seminar — Idea Engineering", "rootNodeId": "seminar-root", "nodes": {"seminar-root": {"id": "seminar-root", "parentId": null, "name": "Idea Engineering — A New Class of AI App (and What Building One with AI Taught Me)", "type": "document", "content": "<p>A seminar for Western Washington University. This is a working skeleton — the structure and the key facts are here; Howard shapes the voice and the stories on top of it.</p><p><strong>The arc in one breath:</strong> everyone uses AI but almost nobody trusts it → a genuinely new category of software is emerging that engineers <em>ideas</em>, not just answers → here is that tool (IdeaM) → here is the honest story of building it <em>with</em> AI → here is the discipline that makes AI output trustworthy → here is why a university should care → live demo and the reveal.</p>", "childrenIds": ["sec-category", "sec-tool", "sec-hook", "sec-casestudy", "sec-why", "sec-takeaways", "sec-demo", "sec-appendix"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": ""}, "sec-hook": {"id": "sec-hook", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "The AI Paradox", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Open with the contradiction everyone in the room feels but hasn't named. In the 2025 Stack Overflow Developer Survey, roughly <strong>80% of developers now use AI</strong> in their work — yet only about <strong>29% actually trust</strong> the accuracy of what it produces, and around <strong>45% say they lose time debugging AI-generated code</strong>.</p><p>So: everyone uses it; almost nobody trusts it. That gap is the whole talk. <strong>Why do we lean on a tool we don't trust — and what would it take to close that gap?</strong></p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "1"}, "sec-category": {"id": "sec-category", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "A New Category: Idea Engineering", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Most AI apps do one narrow thing. Chatbots answer questions. Copilots autocomplete code. Useful, but narrow.</p><p>A new class of software does something bigger: it <strong>engineers ideas</strong>. It takes a raw thought, develops it into a real, structured idea, produces finished work from it, and publishes that work. Call it <strong>&ldquo;the engineering of thought.&rdquo;</strong></p><p>This is not note-taking and not chat. It's a <strong>workbench that turns a thought into finished, published product</strong>. IdeaM is the first tool of this class.</p>", "childrenIds": ["cat-arc", "cat-first"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "2"}, "cat-arc": {"id": "cat-arc", "parentId": "sec-category", "name": "The distinction that matters", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Chatbot: you ask, it answers, the value evaporates when you close the tab. Copilot: it finishes your line of code. Idea Engineering: it carries a single thought all the way from spark to published work, and everything it makes is <em>yours</em> and stays connected. The unit of value isn't a message — it's a finished idea.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "a"}, "cat-first": {"id": "cat-first", "parentId": "sec-category", "name": "Why “a new class” is the right frame", "type": "document", "content": "<p>New categories of software don't get announced; they get recognized in hindsight (the spreadsheet, the web browser, the search engine). Naming the category now — Idea Engineering — is the intellectually honest and the strategically useful move. IdeaM is the first instance, not the whole category.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "b"}, "sec-tool": {"id": "sec-tool", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "The Tool: What Idea Engineering Looks Like", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Walk the audience through the arc concretely, using IdeaM.</p><p><strong>Bring in any source</strong> — video, PDF, web page, audio, email. → <strong>Research &amp; synthesize</strong> across those sources. → <strong>Develop the idea</strong> — this is the engineering step, where a rough thought becomes a structured, defensible whole. → <strong>Produce</strong> — writing, a podcast, a video. → <strong>Publish everywhere in your own voice.</strong> → Even <strong>handle the correspondence</strong> that follows.</p><p>Two commitments underneath it all: <strong>privacy-first, on-device AI</strong>, and <strong>bring-your-own-key</strong> — your ideas and your data stay yours.</p>", "childrenIds": ["tool-arc", "tool-capabilities", "tool-privacy", "tool-university"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "3"}, "tool-arc": {"id": "tool-arc", "parentId": "sec-tool", "name": "The full arc — source to published work", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Source in (any format) → research &amp; synthesize → develop (engineer the idea) → produce (write / podcast / video) → publish in your own voice → manage the correspondence. One continuous pipeline instead of a dozen disconnected apps and copy-paste between them.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "a"}, "tool-privacy": {"id": "tool-privacy", "parentId": "sec-tool", "name": "Privacy-first, on-device, bring-your-own-key", "type": "document", "content": "<p>The AI can run on the user's own device, and users bring their own API key. This isn't a footnote — for researchers, students, and anyone with sensitive or unpublished work, &ldquo;your ideas never leave your control&rdquo; is the difference between a toy and a serious instrument.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "b"}, "tool-university": {"id": "tool-university", "parentId": "sec-tool", "name": "Why universities care", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Turning thoughts into structured, defensible, communicable work <em>is</em> the core academic act — it's what a thesis, a paper, a lecture, and a dissertation all are. Idea Engineering is both a <strong>tool</strong> and a <strong>discipline</strong> for thinkers, researchers, and students. A university is, in effect, an idea-engineering institution that never had the software.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "c"}, "sec-casestudy": {"id": "sec-casestudy", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "The Case Study: Building IdeaM with AI", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Now turn the tool around and tell the story of how it was built — because that story is itself the proof.</p><p>A <strong>solo founder</strong>. Roughly <strong>135,000 lines of code</strong>. Largely <strong>AI-built</strong>. The honest question a skeptical room will ask: is it any good, or is it a house of cards?</p>", "childrenIds": ["case-audit", "case-frontier"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "4"}, "case-audit": {"id": "case-audit", "parentId": "sec-casestudy", "name": "The honest audit", "type": "document", "content": "<p>An independent-style architecture audit graded the codebase a <strong>B</strong> — <strong>above the median</strong> for hand-written production code. <strong>Zero circular dependencies across 388 files.</strong> Clean, modular architecture. The one real blemish: a few oversized “god-files” that do too much — the universal debt of fast development, AI-built or not. Don't hide it; naming the flaw is what makes the grade believable.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "a"}, "case-frontier": {"id": "case-frontier", "parentId": "sec-casestudy", "name": "The frontier — assisted vs. driven", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Draw the line the industry blurs. About <strong>80% of developers use AI as an assistant</strong> (it helps; the human still writes most of it). Only an estimated <strong>10&ndash;25% of development is truly AI-driven</strong> — real &ldquo;vibe coding,&rdquo; where AI does the heavy lifting and the human directs. IdeaM sits in that roughly <strong>15% frontier</strong>. This isn't autocomplete-with-extra-steps; it's a different way of building.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "b"}, "sec-why": {"id": "sec-why", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "Why It Works: The Discipline", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Return to the paradox from the opening and answer it. The reason 45% lose time debugging AI output is that they <em>prompt and hope</em>. The fix is not a better model — it's a <strong>discipline</strong>.</p><p><strong>AI + discipline = trustworthy output.</strong> That equation is the heart of the talk.</p>", "childrenIds": ["why-practices", "why-lesson"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "5"}, "why-practices": {"id": "why-practices", "parentId": "sec-why", "name": "The practices", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Concretely, what &ldquo;discipline&rdquo; means in this project:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Tiered testing</strong> — deterministic code is tested once; AI-powered features are run <strong>5&times;</strong> and checked for <em>invariants</em> (did it stay true to the rules?) rather than an exact-match string.</p></li><li><p><strong>Adversarial guardrails</strong> on anything touching money or privacy — assume the AI will try the wrong thing and block it.</p></li><li><p><strong>An always-on hallucination verifier</strong> checking AI output for invented facts.</p></li><li><p><strong>&ldquo;Review before you trust&rdquo;</strong> — a human reads the output before it counts.</p></li><li><p><strong>Periodic refactoring</strong> and <strong>keeping coupling low</strong> so the codebase stays healthy as it grows.</p></li></ul>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "a"}, "why-lesson": {"id": "why-lesson", "parentId": "sec-why", "name": "The lesson for students", "type": "document", "content": "<p>AI-first development is <strong>not magic</strong> and it is <strong>not a threat to skill</strong> — it is a <strong>new discipline</strong>. The skill shifts from writing every line to <strong>directing and verifying</strong>. Don't just prompt; <strong>direct and verify.</strong> That sentence is the one students should leave with.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "b"}, "sec-takeaways": {"id": "sec-takeaways", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "Takeaways for the University", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Land the talk with something for each part of the room.</p>", "childrenIds": ["take-students", "take-cs", "take-institution"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "6"}, "take-students": {"id": "take-students", "parentId": "sec-takeaways", "name": "For students & researchers", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Idea Engineering is a <strong>skill and a tool</strong>: think faster, produce more, publish in your own voice, and keep it private. It's leverage on the exact work a degree is made of.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "a"}, "take-cs": {"id": "take-cs", "parentId": "sec-takeaways", "name": "For CS students", "type": "document", "content": "<p>AI-first development is a <strong>discipline to master</strong> — architecture, testing, verification — <strong>not a shortcut to fear</strong>. The graduates who thrive won't be the ones who can out-type the AI; they'll be the ones who can direct and verify it.</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "b"}, "take-institution": {"id": "take-institution", "parentId": "sec-takeaways", "name": "For the institution", "type": "document", "content": "<p>A new category of software is being born. The opportunity is to be <strong>the university that understands and adopts it early</strong> — including a possible <strong>student and faculty pilot of IdeaM</strong>. (This is the gentle, concrete ask.)</p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "c"}, "sec-demo": {"id": "sec-demo", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "Live Demo & the Mic-Drop", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Show, don't tell. Run IdeaM live — take a source through the arc to a produced, published piece in front of the room.</p><p>Then the reveal: <strong>this entire seminar was built in IdeaM.</strong> The outline on the screen, the structure, the notes — all of it. <strong>The medium is the message.</strong></p>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "7"}, "sec-appendix": {"id": "sec-appendix", "parentId": "seminar-root", "name": "The Numbers & the Sources", "type": "document", "content": "<p>Everything defensible, in one place, so Howard can answer a pointed question without fumbling.</p>", "childrenIds": ["app-sources", "app-numbers"], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "8"}, "app-sources": {"id": "app-sources", "parentId": "sec-appendix", "name": "Sources", "type": "document", "content": "<ul><li><p><strong>2025 Stack Overflow Developer Survey</strong> — ~80% AI adoption; ~29% trust in accuracy; ~45% report losing time debugging AI output.</p></li><li><p><strong>IdeaM architecture / modularity audit</strong> — Grade B, above median, zero circular dependencies, a few oversized files.</p></li><li><p><strong>Line count</strong> — ~135,000 lines of code, solo founder, largely AI-built.</p></li><li><p><strong>Assisted vs. driven</strong> — ~80% use AI as an assistant; ~10&ndash;25% of development is truly AI-driven; IdeaM in the ~15% frontier.</p></li></ul>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "a"}, "app-numbers": {"id": "app-numbers", "parentId": "sec-appendix", "name": "The numbers at a glance", "type": "document", "content": "<ul><li><p>80% use AI &middot; 29% trust it &middot; 45% lose time debugging it</p></li><li><p>135,000 lines &middot; solo founder &middot; Grade B &middot; zero circular dependencies</p></li><li><p>80% AI-assisted &middot; 10&ndash;25% AI-driven &middot; ~15% frontier</p></li><li><p>AI-feature tests run 5&times; with invariant checks</p></li></ul>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": "b"}, "tool-capabilities": {"id": "tool-capabilities", "parentId": "sec-tool", "name": "What it produces: one idea, many formats", "type": "text", "content": "<ul><li><p>One outline becomes <strong>~13 finished formats</strong>, each in a single click.</p></li><li><p>Written article, executive summary, email, podcast, video, and this slide deck.</p></li><li><p>Plus posts tailored for <strong>7 social platforms</strong>: X, LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, Threads, Bluesky, Reddit.</p></li><li><p>Every output in <strong>your own voice</strong>, in up to <strong>21 languages</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Opt-in privacy</strong>: on-device AI and bring-your-own-key — your ideas never leave your control.</p></li><li><p>An <strong>always-on verifier</strong> checks every draft for invented facts.</p></li></ul>", "childrenIds": [], "isCollapsed": false, "prefix": ""}}, "isGuide": false, "lastModified": 1784892339101}